Spermatheca (
Fig. 73
): spermathecal structure complex, distinct in specimens from the United Arab Emirates (not in specimens from France ), apparently with a large rounded atrium followed by a short, lightly sclerotised calyx; major duct wide and minor duct apparently corresponding to a duct with rough wall.

Legs (
Fig. 77
): leg pretarsi I–IV each with a pair of claws and pulvillus with three rounded lobules. Leg IV with three macrosetae on genu (
ad 2
), basitarsus (
pd 3
) and telotarsus (
pd 2
), all smooth. Leg chaetotaxy (trochanter to tibia): I: 1 , 0/ 1, 1 / 2, 1 ; 2, 3 / 2, 2 / 1, 2 ; 2, 3 / 2, 3 / 1, 2 ; 2, 3 / 2, 3 / 1, 2 ; II: 1 , 0/ 1 , 0/ 2, 1 ; 2, 3 / 1, 2 / 2, 1 ; 2, 3 / 1, 2 / 1, 2 ; 2, 2 / 1, 2 / 1, 2 ; III: 1, 1 / 1, 1 / 1 , 0; 1, 2 / 1, 1 / 0, 1 ; 2, 2 / 1, 2 / 1, 1 ; 2, 1 / 1, 2 / 1, 1 ; IV: 1, 1 / 1 , 0/ 1, 1 ; 1, 2 / 1, 1 / 0, 1 ; 2, 2 / 1, 3 / 0, 1 ; 2, 1 / 1, 3 / 1, 2 .

